<Defs>

  <!--============================ Andrium ===============================-->

  <ThingDef ParentName="RockBase">
    <defName>MineableAndrium</defName>
    <label>andrium ore</label>
    <description>Rock containing bits of andrium.

A very heavy, but sturdy material, that is spoken of in legend as being one of the most durable materials in the known universe. It is also known as one of the most volatile, where unprocessed Andrium will violently explode if put under too much stress. This volativity makes it very hard to work with, and its heavy weight makes it ill suited for anything that need to move, as well as protective armor. Its volatile nature makes it very valuable to those intending to weaponize the material, and could probably be used as an improvised explosive.

Dedicated to: andrethegodkiller</description>
    <graphicData>
      <texPath>Things/Building/Linked/RockFlecked_Atlas</texPath>
      <graphicClass>Graphic_Single</graphicClass>
      <shaderType>CutoutComplex</shaderType>
      <color>(46,25,25)</color> <!--#2e1919-->
      <colorTwo>(115,12,14)</colorTwo> <!--#730c0e-->
    </graphicData>
    <statBases>
      <MaxHitPoints>5700</MaxHitPoints>
    </statBases>
	<scatterableOnMapGen>false</scatterableOnMapGen>
    <building>
		<isResourceRock>true</isResourceRock>
		<mineableThing>Andrium</mineableThing>
		<mineableYield>42</mineableYield>
		<mineableScatterCommonality>0.01</mineableScatterCommonality>
		<mineableScatterLumpSizeRange>8~26</mineableScatterLumpSizeRange>
    </building>
  </ThingDef>

  <!--============================ Bananite ===============================-->

  <ThingDef ParentName="RockBase">
    <defName>MineableBananite</defName>
    <label>bananite ore</label>
    <description>Rock containing bits of bananite.

Slippery to the touch, making it exceptional for use in anything that needs to move. This trait does make it rather useless for weapon crafting, as the slippery surface makes it harder to handle, and easy to drop by accident. The green sheen, from which this yellow ore gets its name, makes it a very pretty metal, and rich merchants might even make entire rooms out of this material, just to show off. This material will deteriorate if not stored properly, making it self-disintigrate if left unattended.

Dedicated to: bananamove</description>
    <graphicData>
      <texPath>Things/Building/Linked/RockFlecked_Atlas</texPath>
      <graphicClass>Graphic_Single</graphicClass>
      <shaderType>CutoutComplex</shaderType>
